# Security / Data Integrity Rules

## Secrets
- Never commit secrets, tokens, credentials, private keys, production data, or real uploads.
- Never log secrets or sensitive payloads.

## Authorization
- Enforce establishment isolation server-side.
- Validate active membership before access.
- Validate role and BusinessUnit scope before mutations.
- Frontend checks are UX only, never security.

## Uploads/media
- Validate real file content, not only declared MIME.
- Enforce size/type limits.
- Use private storage and signed URLs.
- Do not expose raw storage paths.
- Do not send observation photos to AI unless product contract changes.

## Async/realtime
- Celery tasks must be safe to retry.
- WebSocket events must validate participant/membership access.
- Broadcast minimal payloads.

## AI/data
- Send minimum necessary context.
- Do not leak raw sensitive data in logs or prompts.
- Preserve retention rules.

## Destructive actions
- Prefer blocked delete or soft delete when linked business records exist.
- Hard delete only when product contract explicitly allows it.